  "text": "These data show that combining simple measurements of placental or fetal dry and wet weights correlates with maternal diet and may reflect fetal nutrition that reflects post-natal growth and correlates with mtDNA content. They show that the detrimental effect of maternal LPD on placental efficiency is not due to a deficiency of either placental mtDNA or ATP. For the first time, using LPD and NPD we have shown that placental mtDNA is highest in the least successful litters, perhaps because mtDNA copy number increases in oxidative stress [CITATION_1] .",
